name: Dr. James Moreau
about: After completing his initial degree at the University of New Orleans, Dr. Moreau pursued his dental doctorate at the Louisiana State University School of Dentistry. Today, he is a proud Diplomate of the American Academy of Dental Sleep Medicine and a Fellow of the Academy of General Dentistry. He is also eligible for a Fellowship with the International College of Cranio-Mandibular Orthopedics and a current member of the American Dental Association and Louisiana Dental Association. Over the decades, he has remained committed to pursuing continuing education at very opportunity, including courses about laser dentistry, dental implants, oral surgery, prosthetics, root canals, orthodontics, advanced life support, and much more. He considers himself a “Swiss Army Knife” of a dentist!

questionResponses.response:
After over 40 years of practicing, Dr. Moreau is still expanding his expertise to be able to offer patients the best comprehensive care he can. 

Are you a person who likes a lot of details or do you prefer the bottomline? Patients love Dr. Moreau's ability to understand their communication style, allowing him to educate patients on their dental needs in a way they best take in information.

question.question: Why should patients choose you as their provider instead of others in the area
question.example: I've been practicing dentistry for over 17 years, and treat a wide range of issues. Our practices focuses on making sure that you are 100% involved in your healthcare choices, and that you always feel safe and comfortable. Our practice also offers a wide range of payment options to match your needs.

questionResponses.response: While Dr. Moreau has expertise in all areas of general dentistry, his primary focuses include cosmetic dentistry, treatment of oral sleep disorders and TMJ disorder (head and neck pain), and implant placement and restorations.

question.question: What are the top 3 treatments that you focus on
question.example: I am skilled in all areas of dentistry, but primarily focus on Cosmetics, Invisalign, Oral Surgery and Teeth Whitening in my practice. I believe very strongly in continuing my education and completing advanced training programs in Orthodontics, Periodontics, Endodontics and Cosmetic Dentistry to make sure I can provide the highest quality of dentistry to all my patients.

questionResponses.response: Dr. Moreau founded MoreSMILES Dental Spa in 2000 and designed the practice and facility with the patient's comfort and relaxation in mind.

question.question: What are you proud of in your practice
question.example: Something that makes me very proud is that our practice has good reviews because of our experienced staff, attractive aesthetics and advanced equipment. It's fully accessible and designed for geriatric care and patients with mobility issues.

clinic.name: MoreSmiles Dental Spa
clinic.description:
We provide comprehensive dental care for all your family's needs. Our services range from emergency and preventive care all the way to complex, full-mouth reconstruction, cosmetics, sleep-breathing disorders, dentures, and dental implants. Our dentists have the skills, the training, and the experience to give you the results you’re looking for. And our professional team provides competence with efficiency and finesse. Our five-star service is a benchmark in health care delivery.

Advance through the photos below to see what our dental office looks like, and contact our dentistry team today to request an appointment with our skilled dentists and caring team!
